COLORATION (
Fig. 1A
). — Antennular and antennal peduncles orangish-red; ocular peduncles red, cornea black. Chelipeds (
Fig. 3A
) and ambulatory legs (
Fig. 4A
) with bright red rings, alternating with narrower yellow rings; red rings present on chelae (including fingers), dactyls, propodi, carpi and meri. Propodi of ambulatory legs each with a distal red ring along anterior margin and 5 or 6 subsequent red rings (sometimes divided by yellow lines). Shield pure white; abdomen red with a pattern of undulating yellow lines.
